reply.p:
In respect of other transactions with my Department, a person must also satisfy the Minister as to their identity:-
Before they can be allocated and issued a Personal Public Service Number (PPSN);
Before they can be issued a Public Services Card;
To continue to receive benefit , once they have been requested to satisfy the Minister as to their identity.In respect of transactions with other specified bodies where one of those bodies requests or accepts the PSC as proof of identity from a person, it is important to note that, since its inception in the late 1990s, the PSC has always been intended to be used as physical token of identity to be used in transactions between the citizens and the State, not just between citizens and my Department.
